66 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\",\"key\":\"1s2grr\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M20 2v4\",\"key\":\"1rf3ol\"}],[\"path\",{\"d\":\"M22 4h-4\",\"key\":\"gwowj6\"}],[\"circle\",{\"cx\":\"4\",\"cy\":\"20\",\"r\":\"2\",\"key\":\"6kqj1y\"}]],\"className\":\"lucide-sparkles h-8 w-8\"}]}],\"$L6\",\"$L7\"]}]}],\"$L8\",\"$L9\",\"$La\",\"$Lb\"]}]]]}]}],[\"$Lc\"],\"$Ld\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"UiGyDcZs6FHpn-bosIzqQ\"}\n6:[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-950 sm:text-6xl\",\"children\":[\"Names That Mean \",\"Love\"]}]\n7:[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-600\",\"children\":\"Names signifying affection, care, and deep emotional connection—perfect for a child who will be cherished.\"}]\n8:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-8 px-4 py-12 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_340px]\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"className\":\"prose prose-lg max-w-none\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"Names that mean love help parents connect a child's identity with a clear emotional, spiritual, or cultural value. On NameVerse, this meaning page is built only from names already present in the database, so every linked name has an existing profile, religion, origin, and meaning field. The collection currently includes 3 database entries, beginning with names such as Amina, Priya, Agape.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"The love theme appears across multiple naming traditions. islamic (15), hindu (15), christian (15) each express this value through different linguistic roots, historical usage, and family expectations. A name from this meaning group may be chosen because the sound fits the family, the origin matches cultural heritage, or the meaning reflects a hope parents want to carry forward.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"2\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"When browsing names that mean love, compare the short meaning with the full origin context. Two names can share the same core meaning while feeling very different in pronunciation, gender association, religious usage, and cultural history. NameVerse keeps the name pages connected so you can move from this meaning hub to individual name meanings without losing context.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"3\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"The most useful way to choose from this collection is to start with the meaning, then narrow by religion, origin, gender, and first letter. Parents often want a name that is meaningful but also easy to pronounce, spell, and use across school, work, and family settings. Each linked name page provides deeper details such as lucky number, origin, pronunciation, and related collections.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"4\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"This meaning page also supports internal discovery. Related meaning pages help you explore adjacent values, while religion pages show the broader naming tradition. Story pages and blog guides add editorial context for parents who want to understand naming customs, trends, and cultural background before choosing a final shortlist.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"5\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"NameVerse treats meaning pages as collection hubs rather than thin keyword pages. The page lists real names, explains how the meaning is used across traditions, connects to related meanings, and points to deeper guides. That structure helps search engines understand the page topic while giving users a practical path from inspiration to detailed research.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"6\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"If you are building a shortlist, save names that share the love meaning but vary in origin and sound. For example, one option may be short and modern, while another may be traditional and heritage-focused. Comparing several options from the same meaning group makes it easier to find a name that feels personal without sacrificing cultural accuracy.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"7\",{\"className\":\"text-base leading-8 text-slate-700\",\"children\":\"The love collection will grow as new verified names are added to the database. Because the page is generated from existing name records, it does not invent meanings or create pages for values that are not already represented. This keeps the meaning architecture scalable for tens of thousands of names while preserving trust and consistency.\"}]]}],\"$Le\"]}]\n9:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-6 flex items-center justify-between\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-slate-500\",\"children\":\"Related meaning pages\"}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-display text-3xl font-bold text-slate-950\",\"children\":\"Explore adjacent meanings\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"href\":\"/names-by-meaning\",\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-slate-950 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-white\",\"children\":\"All meanings\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"strength\",{\"href\":\"/meaning/strength\",\"className\":\"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm transition hover:-translate-y-1 hover:border-emerald-300\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-slate-900\",\"children\":[\"Names That Mean \"